Kenyan Olympic Marathon Champion Wanjiru Killed After Falling From Balcony

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-05-16T05:13:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-16/kenyan-olympic-marathon-champion-wanjiru-killed-after-falling-from-balcony.html
Kenyan Olympic marathon champion
Sammy Wanjiru died after falling from a balcony at his home in
Rift Valley province, a police official said. He was 24.  The incident occurred at around 11:30 p.m. yesterday in
Nyahururu, 155 kilometers (96 miles) northwest of Nairobi, the
capital, Jasper Ombati, police commander for Nyandarua County,
said in a phone interview today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  